-- Vivendi’s SFR and Bull Form Cloud Computing Company, Echos Says
-- B y   R u d y   R u i t e n b e r g
-- 2012-05-10T05:18:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-10/vivendi-s-sfr-and-bull-form-cloud-computing-company-echos-says.html
SFR SA,  Vivendi SA (VIV) ’s French mobile-
phone unit, will set up a company to offer cloud-computing
services with computer maker  Bull (BULL)  SA, Les Echos reported,
without saying where it got the information.  France is backing the project through a stake purchase by
state investment company Caisse des Depots et Consignations, the
newspaper said. SFR will own 47 percent, Bull 20 percent and CDC
33 percent of the company, with a capital of 225 million euros
($291 million), according to Les Echos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rudy Ruitenberg in Paris at +33-1-5365-5039 or
 rruitenberg@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
